<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF5ACE8AFF77F912DA123BF4" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF5ACE8AFF77F912DA123BF4" blockId="215.[136,778,1731,2082]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5ACE8AFF77F912DA513AF3" bold="true" box="[136,258,1731,1757]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5ACE8AFE32F915DB863B2C" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="215" pageNumber="216" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, males of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5ACE8AFEB5F939D9703B2C" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[330,547,1768,1794]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balcarce">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5ACE8AFEB5F939D9703B2C" box="[330,547,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Actinopus balcarce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5ACE8AFF77F8DDDA593B08" authorityName="Rios" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,266,1804,1830]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5ACE8AFF77F8DDDA593B08" box="[136,266,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">A. goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5ACE8AFEE7F8DDDAC73B08" author="Rios, D. T." box="[280,404,1804,1830]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" pagination="73 - 77" refId="ref140396" refString="Rios, D. T. (2014) A new species of the genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) from Argentina. Acta Arachnologica, 63 (2): 73 - 77. https: // doi. org / 10.2476 / asjaa. 63.73" type="journal article" year="2014">Ríos, 2014</bibRefCitation>
, figs 6–8) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5ACE8AFDCCF8DDD9ED3B08" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[563,702,1804,1830]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavatus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5ACE8AFDCCF8DDD9ED3B08" box="[563,702,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">A. excavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018, fig. 39 E–G) by having BTA well developed, PA porly developed (
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5ACE8AFDB2F885DA643BBC" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="215" pageNumber="216" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 38 D–F) and by the lower number of retrolateral thorns on tibia II (
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5ACE8AFE22F84DDB903BF4" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="215" pageNumber="216" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 38 B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
